body:
I have tried with 0.12.0 and it failed in the same way. The I trace and log the exception like this.

```
ipdb> pp e
InvalidArgumentError()
ipdb> pp e.error_code
3
ipdb> pp e.message
u'You must feed a value for placeholder tensor \'Placeholder_2\' with dtype float\n\t [[Node: Placeholder_2 = Placeholder[dtype=DT_FLOAT, shape=[], _device="/job:master/replica:0/task:0/cpu:0"]()]]'
ipdb> e.op
<tensorflow.python.framework.ops.Operation object at 0x7ff87957a050>
```

I was trying to export the generic signature and not sure why it need to feed the placeholder. It's caused by this line of code while it works in standalone mode.

```
exporter.generic_signature({"keys": keys_placeholder,
                                                  "X": X})
```

It still failed even I try to export nothing in signature. May not be related to `exporter`.

```
              model_exporter = exporter.Exporter(saver)
              model_exporter.init(
                  sess.graph.as_graph_def(),
                  named_graph_signatures={
                      'inputs':
                      exporter.generic_signature({}),
                      'outputs':
                      exporter.generic_signature({})
                  })
              model_exporter.export(FLAGS.model_path,
                                    tf.constant(FLAGS.model_version), sess)
```
